d here that, though non-duality is the truth even during the time of seemin=
g ignorance, this does not mean that no spiritual practice (sadhana) is nec=
essary,as some theoreticians/ theorists have wrongly concluded.So long as t=
he tenth man appears to be lost, it is necessary for each one of the ten to=
 enquire and find out =E2=80=98Who is lost?=E2=80=99 , for then only will t=
he truth be realized that the so called =E2=80=98lost=E2=80=99 tenth man is=
 only oneself, who has in fact never been lost. Similarly, so long as the e=
xperience of non-duality appears to be lost, it is necessary for us to enqu=
ire and find out =E2=80=98Who am I, who have lost the experience of non-dua=
lity?=E2=80=99, for then only will the truth be realized that the seeming i=
ndividual =E2=80=98I=E2=80=99 who does not experience non-duality is merely=
 an unreal appearance, and that the real =E2=80=98I=E2=80=99 has in fact ne=
ver lost the experience of non-duality.

